@saladshootavvv
You can still use symphony, concerto, nocturne, dirge, minuet, bolero, sonata, requiem, aria, prelude, serenade or whatever to describe a piece in a setting where that would actually matter; nothing is stopping you from doing that.
Really though, the things I've listed work just as well as sub-genres under 'classical music'. So I'm just going to call them classical songs that just happen to be symphonies or serenades. That is how it is going to be.

@saladshootavvv
